<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 9: LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTER AND
        COOLER - LUBRICATING OIL PUMP - INSPECTION AND REPAIR
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="3">
        <title>INSPECTION AND REPAIR</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Visually inspect the rotors, housing and plate for nicks, burrs or scoring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace any damaged components.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The inner and outer rotors are a matched set and cannot be replaced separately.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect for wear by checking the radial clearance between the outer rotor and the pump
                housing using a feeler gauge as shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600908">9.8</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                . Refer to "
                <emph type="bold">SPECIFICATIONS</emph>". If radial clearance exceeds the specifications, check housing
                to rotor clearance (see step 4).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check housing to rotor clearance as follows: Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600909">9.9</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">With the O-Ring removed from the oil pump housing, place a straightedge across the
                    housing.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Insert an appropriate feeler gauge under the straightedge (
                    <emph type="bold">OEM1293</emph>) at the housing and outer rotor. (See "
                    <emph type="bold">SPECIFICATIONS</emph>".)
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If not within specifications, check the housing and inner rotor for wear. Replace worn
                    components, as required.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600907" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5096" filename="../figeg5/EG5096.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.7 Remove Oil Pump Housing Plate</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. O-Ring</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Oil Pump Plate</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600908" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5209" filename="../figeg5/EG5209.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.8 Inspect Rotors For Wear</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600909" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5210" filename="../figeg5/EG5210.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.9 Checking Housing/Rotor Clearance</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
